A '''boscage''' is a place set with [[tree]]s; a [[Grove (nature)|grove]] or [[thicket]]. In a legal sense, it signifies mast&mdash;nuts of forest trees, used as food for pigs&mdash;or any such sustenance as wood and trees yield to cattle.

Among painters, the term is used for a picture depicting a wooded scene.

